        <num>CC 1411</num>
        <heading>1411.  Rescission inadmissible against partition regulated by father</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1411.  Rescission inadmissible against partition regulated by father.
If the partition has been regulated by the father among his children, no restitution can take place, even in favor of minors, when, by such partition, one or more of the heirs have received more than the others, unless that overplus should exceed the portion which the father had a right to dispose of.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
